$interpreted: Clark: I...Maria, I know I'm usually lazy, but...
Clark: I still prefer to walk myself...can you put me down...?
Maria: No. C-C-C-Clark is injured. You need to behave.
Clark: But...I...Headmaster Ceres is here too...this is so embarrassing...
Hutchinson: Not at all. Giving the lady a chance to shine is also required of elegant gentlemen.
Ru-yi: That's right. Plus, we're moving much faster this way. We've got to get back and find Rune as soon as possible!
Clark: I'm sorry I can't run that fast...
Sophie: That idiot! Running around with an injury like that, when I see him I'm gonna give him a good beating!
Clark: ...eh. To be honest, Rune's skin is pretty tough. I'm pretty sure if you beat him your hand is the only thing that is going to be hurting...
Sophie: Don't talk to me if I don't ask you to!
Ru-yi: ...I've never seen such a terrifying Sophie...
Hutchinson: There's an old saying...everyone has a skeleton in their closet...
Hanbei: ...Best to just stay out of their way...
Charle: Look out!
Officer: A deer, a whale, and a mouse...
Officer: Looks like you're the circus the general was talking about.
Hanbei: How rude! Who are you calling a mouse!?
Sophie: What are you going to do about it?
Officer: The general has ordered that you are not to approach the Desert Kingdom.
Charle: And if we insist?
Officer: Then you'll enter as nothing more than cold, dead bodies.
Sophie: Ugh...no way...we're barely holding on as it is.!
Soldier: WAHHHH!!!!
Sophie: That's...
Rune: ...So...phie...you're alive...wonderful.
Sophie: No. Not at all!!! Did you even think about your own safety? Why are you always this impulsive!?
Sophie: You know what I hate the most!? People who sacrifice themselves to help others!!
Rune: Sophie...you're more than that...Sophie and Sanchez are...a part of me...
Rune: ...Sanchez is...dead...
Rune: ...The future...I don't ever want to not see Sophie again...why is Sophie...angry...I don't understand...
Sophie: ......
Rune: Sophie?
Sophie: ...I'm sorry. I shouldn't yell at you without making things clear.
Sophie: ——Thank you for coming to save me.
Charle: ...Clark. Is that the New City you told us about?
Clark: Eh?
Charle: Look over there!
Sophie: Are those the birds from the Shrine? Why did they start flying all of a sudden?
Rune: ...Activated...
Sophie: Rune?
Rune: That's what Nikola said.
Rune: ——If it's activated, everybody will die.
